<Review ID>5156099
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Red)
<Title>Mine was defective.
<Date>Fri Feb 08 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>Even though my Sansa Clip ended up being defective (worked fine for a few days, then wouldn't hold a charge for more than a couple hours and then it just stopped working completely after only a couple weeks), I'm still giving it 4 stars.  I'm just baffled by the sound that this puppy puts out.  "Awesome" is the only way to put it!  Pros: 1.  Compact size 2.  AWESOME sound 3.  I love having the radio option 4.  Holds a lot of songs 5.  The price is great 6.  I love the whole look/design of it. 7.  Easy to operate  Cons: 1.  The earphones (I should note that the previous review calling them "Earbuds" could be misleading, they are not actually Earbud brand, just the "generic" ones you get with pretty much everything)  2.  The rechargeable battery cannot be replaced so, down the road, once it dies, it's done. 3.  USB charging... I'm not a fan of this idea in general 4.  Instructions included only covered the very basics.  Would have liked the actual manual that you can find on SanDisk's site. 5.  The clip isn't strong enough to use during vigorous exercise without it falling off.  I end up just putting it in my pocket, if I have one.  Despite the cons, I love this thing!  Here's to hoping that my replacement won't turn out to be defective as well.  
<Overall>4

