<Review ID>8532455
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Red)
<Title>A great start on a promising product
<Date>Sun Feb 17 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>The Sansa Clip 2Gb unit is a very good alternative to the popular iPod devices.  It is particularly good for joggers due to it's small size and the securing clip feature.  I actually have two units, one is 1Gb and the other 2Gb.  They integrate nicely with the Windows (XP or Vista) environment.  The sound quality is excellent when used with good quality ear buds or high-quality earphones (I have tested both).  The downside is the ear buds provided with the unit are not the best quality, but better quality ear buds are readily available at low cost.  The "quick start" quide provided with the unit has minimal information, and does not clearly point out that a full user manual is available at the manufacturer's Web site.  I discovered this later independently.  One positive here is that once you access that web site and install the microcode update software, the rest then becomes automatic and simple (but the enclosed documentation when you first get the unit is not very clear about this).  My main requests for improvement would include improving the original quick start documentation to make sure the user understands that the best way to proceed is to go to the company web site first.  My second request would be to provide this package size with much higher memory size, I would say at least 8Gb.  I love the small size of the unit since I play only music, not videos, which I think are not worthy of watching on a small screen.  By next year I think we can hope memory costs will be low enough to make this happen.  
<Overall>4

