<Review ID>0052855
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Red)
<Title>I just love my Sansa Clip!
<Date>Tue Feb 26 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>When my 4-yr-old Ipod Mini's battery died, I found it would cost me big bucks to have it replaced. I looked around Amazon for reviews of cheaper MP3 players.  OK, I have to admit that I liked the red color and cute mini-Ipod look of the Sansa Clip. But the reviews were good, and the cost significantly less than just replacing the battery of the defunct Ipod. So... I bit and ordered.  I have been using it daily for going on 2 months now, and think it was a great buy. It set up and interfaces easily with Windows Media Player. It is small and lightweight and tucks easily into a pocket, or clips to a collar, lapel, etc. I've dropped it a time or two, with no effect, so appears to be pretty sturdy. The 2 GB is less than my Ipod, but I just synch often to change things around. I have to anyway to keep up with podcasts. The sound is great, with plenty of volume. The battery charge lasts for a looooong time.  The only thing I miss is that with the Sansa Clip you cannot back up incrementally within a track, as you can with an Ipod (albeit not that easily sometimes). So if that is a must, you'll want to try something else. But that has not been a big problem at all, not worth paying an additional $100-$150 for.  Oh yeah, it is even cuter than it looks in the picture, with a very easily readable, crisp color display that is super-easy to navigate.  
<Overall>5

<Review ID>1733164
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Red)
