<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Red)
<Title>Excellent!
<Date>Mon Jan 14 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>I've had this mp3 player for nearly 2 months now, without any problems. And the price is reasonable, too. I've been hearing about defective units, but don't let that discourage you from buying this little gem! If yours happens to be defective, just exchange it. Sandisk's quality control may not be perfect, but when they get it right, they get it RIGHT.....  Pros: Small & easy to carry Display is easy to read Lots of features Good sound quality Decent battery life Charges in about 3 1/2 hrs(other mp3 players take 6 hrs) Menus are easy to navigate Small & compact Convenient belt clip MSC mode to drag & drop files- a must for Linux users like myself. Fast file transfer- more than 1 GB of songs transferred in roughly 5 minutes!  Cons: User guide isn't very extensive USB cord that comes with the player is only 9 inches long, so I have to use my own. I don't like ear buds, so I use my own Sony headphones.  Overall, this is an excellent player & I'd recommend it to anyone.  
