<Review ID>7215906
<Product Name>SanDisk Sansa Clip 2 GB MP3 Player (Red)
<Title>Awesome!
<Date>Thu Jan 31 00:00:00 CST 2008
<Content>I bought this little mp3 player last Fall because let's face it, I'm in the dark ages without ever having an mp3 player.  I refused to buy an Ipod because the prices are ridiculous.  I found this little gem (2 gb) for $50 at Best Buy.  The only initial problem I had was I was running Media Player 9 and you MUST have 10 in order for your computer to recognize that the Sansa Clip is attached.  (This caused me many days of frustration...I even returned the first Sansca clip, thinking it was defective.  Then Sandisk support saved the day!)  Other than that, this player is awesome!  I use the FM tuner a lot on the bus back and forth to work, and have loaded multiple albums onto it also and still have a lot of room left.  Sound is great -- I don't like earbuds so am using my favorite Sony headphones.  I have nothing bad to say about this unit!  The only thing I can foresee going wrong is the clip breaking because it's made of plastic (why they didn't just make it out of the metal, I have no clue), but since I don't use the clip, this isn't a problem for me.  If you have a pocket, use it :-)  
<Overall>5

